        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35859",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Final example of hole function:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nfunction Example(array $options = null) {\r\n    $permittedOptions = array(\r\n        'where' => null,\r\n        'order' => null,\r\n        'count' => null,\r\n        'offset' => null\r\n    );\r\n    foreach ($options as $key => $val) {\r\n        if (array_key_exists($key, $permittedOptions)) {\r\n            $permittedOptions[$key] = $val;\r\n        } else {\r\n            throw new Exception('Invalid \"' . $key . '\" option.');\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    return Zend_Db_Table_Abstract->fetchAll($permittedOptions['where'], $permittedOptions['order'], $permittedOptions['count'], $permittedOptions['offset']);\r\n}\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-09T04:48:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-09T04:48:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35860",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=robinsk",
                        "name": "robinsk",
                        "displayName": "Robin Skoglund",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I assume you mean this is something that should be implemented throughout the framework, so I set components to 'Unknown' to prevent unnecessary spam notifications to all contributors.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=robinsk",
                        "name": "robinsk",
                        "displayName": "Robin Skoglund",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-09T04:54:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-09T04:54:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35861",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nico",
                        "name": "nico",
                        "displayName": "Nico Edtinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That's something, that should be solved in PHP and not ZF.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nico",
                        "name": "nico",
                        "displayName": "Nico Edtinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-09T04:54:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-09T04:54:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35862",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nico",
                        "name": "nico",
                        "displayName": "Nico Edtinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As you've given an example ... how do I know which parameters are allowed, if they are know hidden in the function body?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nico",
                        "name": "nico",
                        "displayName": "Nico Edtinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-09T04:57:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-09T04:57:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35863",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You can specify them in function's description, as a lot of functions does.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-09T04:58:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-09T04:58:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35864",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes Robin, you assumed it right. This should be implemented throughout the whole framework.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-09T05:08:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-09T05:08:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35869",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This would negotate actual behaviour.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\nYou can give an array or an instance of Zend_Config (which behaves like an array) to Zend_Filter and Zend_Validate classes. A configuration can hold also other keys than the accepted.\r\n\r\nBy throwing an exception you force the user to have multiple configurations, one for each module, instead of one for the application. This is not userfriendly.\r\n\r\nIn my understanding a component should not throw an exception on unknown options, but simply ignore them.\r\nBut it has to throw an exception on missing options when there are no default values.\r\n\r\nAlso to note:\r\nSeveral other components already support to give options as array.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-09T08:21:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-09T08:21:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35872",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I didn't understand why you mentioned multiple configurations, one for each module.\r\n\r\nAll I'm saying is about how to input parameters, not how function works. It's not functional filling in a lot of parameters (that in most of time are default) just to change the last parameter.\r\n\r\nThat function above was just an example. And by the way, the permittedOptions' block I got from a ZF's function (don't remember now wich one). This block is supposed to filter parameters filled in. The excess could be threw in a catch or ignored.\r\n\r\nThe focus here is to reduce the work, allowing less configuration (in this case, data inputing), filling in what's really necessary.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-09T08:40:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-09T08:40:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35936",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hello ?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-11T08:46:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-11T08:46:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35939",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I mentioned multiple configurations because your change would force to have one configuration for each filter or validator.\r\nThey already support giving an array and have the by me described behaviour.\r\n\r\nNormally you would have one configuration like this (only example):\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n$options = array(\r\n    'AllowDNS' => true,\r\n    'ValidateIDN' => true,\r\n    'Length' => 10,\r\n    'AllowUTF8' => false\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nEach validator would use the options which he understands and ignore all others.\r\nThis could also be true for other components.\r\n\r\n@Robin:\r\nWhen you want to have reply from all maintainers like me, then you should not erase the components.\r\nMaintainers which are not affected because their components already support this, will probably erase their components to keep away unwanted replies. ;-)\r\nWhat you described and gave as example would mean that you have to seperate these options for each component(filter in this case). This is what I called not a good behaviour.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-11T12:23:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-11T12:23:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35943",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thomas,\r\n\r\nI understood and accepted your point of view. You are totally right about throwing an exception when function don't recognize a inserted option. That must not happen.\r\n\r\nBut not all functions accept array as parameter's input. Like I said, I think ZF should be revised to accept array's parameters when parameters expected are greater than 2 and are not required.\r\n\r\nWith Zend_Ldap for example, it's already fixed. Now we got Zend_Db_Table_Abstract->fetchAll's function.\r\n\r\nWe could make a list of functions that forces user to input data one-by-one.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-11T15:15:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-11T15:15:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35948",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "To clearify this more closely...\r\n\r\nFunctions overall the framework should accept the following notations:\r\n\r\n - afunction(parametera, parameterb, parameterc)\r\n   * this is needed for IDE's as they are actually not able to give array keys as options\r\n   * when possible default parameters should be used\r\n\r\n - bfunction(array(parametera => valuea, parameterb => valueb, parameterc => valuec))\r\n   * this allows to strip unneeded parameters from being given (default values)\r\n   * and this allows to define the options very simple elsewhere\r\n\r\n - cfunction(Zend_Config)\r\n   * Zend_Config is the frameworks way to provide\/collect\/give options\r\n   * every function should also accept a instance of Zend_Config\r\n\r\nInternally a Zend_Config instance would be downgraded into an array (by a single line within cfunction like Zend_Config->toArray()). Then cfunction has the same behaviour as bfunction when unknown options are ignored.\r\n\r\nThat are my 2 cents.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-12T00:11:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-12T00:11:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35950",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Almost there!\r\n\r\nI believe that not every function should accept a instance of Zend_Config.\r\n\r\nIn case of \"afunction\", parameters should be required and should be given ony-by-one. In another case, user can give options as an array or an instance of Zend_Config.\r\n\r\nResuming, there are 2 ways to input parameters:\r\n\r\na) required parameters -> explicit -> one-by-one -> function(param1, param2, param3)\r\nb) optional parameters -> implicit -> array or Zend_Config -> function(array('param2'=>'value2'))\r\n\r\nBy the way, i checked the meaning of \"That are my 2 cents\" .. It's a 1940's slang! :D\r\n\r\nWell ... That are my 2 cents too!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-12T01:18:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-12T01:18:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36461",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Is this discussion over?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-24T05:24:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-24T05:24:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39443",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The problem is, that you did not attach a related component.\r\n\r\nNote that (almost) all components, where I am the component maintainer, ALREADY support the 3 notations which I described above.\r\n\r\nWhen you want to have progress on this issue I would recommend that you attach the components which you want to have changed\/discussed about.\r\n\r\nOtherwise I would argue that this issue has to be closed as it's not clear what should be changed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-21T10:42:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-21T10:42:00.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
